SIMPLE: peculation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peculation
<hw>Pec`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
practice of peculating, or of defrauding the public by appropriating to
one's own use the money or goods intrusted to one's care for management
or disbursement; embezzlement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every British subject . . . active in the discovery of
<qex>peculations</qex> has been ruined.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peculator</ent>⟦br⟧
